This paper is about video object segmentation using a spatiotemporal CNN model. The paper focuses on designing a model that can capture both spatial and temporal information to accurately segment objects in videos. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adversarial training, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of attention modules, which are commonly used in multimedia analysis and fall under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of fine-tuning, which is a common technique in transfer learning and falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a coarse-to-fine process, which is a common technique in robotics and falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
